@fanzhe98 , this change fails to build on OS-X (it uses the same socket adapter).
For addressing that, one way is to add a define at the top of socketio_berkeley.c:
// MSG_NOSIGNAL is not defined on all platforms where socketio_berkeley.c is used (e.g., OS-X).
// Setting MSG_NOSIGNAL to 0 results in not suppressing SIGPIPE.
#ifndef MSG_NOSIGNAL
#define MSG_NOSIGNAL 0 
#endif
If you do need to have the signal suppressed on OS-X as well, this would be a recourse to be added:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19509348/sigpipe-osx-and-disconnected-sockets

@fanzhe98 this is causing the build to fail.  Why is it passing in the build Azure Sphere is using?  Meaning, I speculate there would be some other code changes in Azure Sphere this depends on that are not included here -- can you please include?
Did you possibly mean to use
(void)name;

If I use the above, our build still compiles.  Does it solve the issue you ran into that required the "unused" patch?

